{{Use Hong Kong English|date=January 2018}} {{Use dmy dates|date=January 2018}} {{Infobox high court | court_name = Hong Kong International Arbitration Centre | native_name = ''香港國際仲裁中心'' | image = HKIAC Logo.gif | imagesize = 150px | caption = Seal of HKIAC | established = 1985 | location = [[Hong Kong]] | coordinates = {{coord|22.283|N|114.158|E}} |region_served = International | website = [http://www.hkiac.org/ hkiac.org] | chiefjudgetitle = Secretary-General | chiefjudgename = Sarah Grimmer<ref name=SG>{{cite web|url=http://www.hkiac.org/news/sarah-grimmer-leads-new-secretary-general/|title=Secretary-General|accessdate=10 November 2016|work=HKIAC}}</ref> | termstart = 2016 | chiefjudgetitle2 = Chairperson | chiefjudgename2 = Matthew Gearing QC | termstart2 = 2017 }} {{Infobox Chinese | t = 香港國際仲裁中心 | y = Hēung góng gwok jai juhng chòih jūng sām | j = Hoeng<sup>1</sup> gong<sup>2</sup> gwok<sup>3</sup> zai<sup>3</sup> zung<sup>6</sup> coi<sup>4</sup> zung<sup>1</sup> sam<sup>1</sup> |hide=yes }}
The '''Hong Kong International Arbitration Centre''' ('''HKIAC''') is an institution based in [[Hong Kong]], providing [[alternative dispute resolution]] services from administered and ad hoc [[arbitration]] to [[mediation]], [[adjudication]] and [[domain name]] dispute resolution. It was founded in 1985.
==History==
The Centre was established in 1985 to promote the use of arbitration and other forms of alternative dispute resolution services in Asia. Formed as a non-profit making company limited by guarantee under Hong Kong law, HKIAC was originally funded with assistance from the business community and the Hong Kong Government. Today, the Centre is independent of both the business community and the Government, and operates with its own budget and funds.<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com.hk/books?id=aq-q9ZHquRYC&pg=PA23&lpg=PA23&dq=history+of+HKIAC&source=bl&ots=9DIY2L7E5T&sig=QNR2NgRC8xCS_1XmdqKVRcpBCrg&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwie6tquzZ_QAhUHjLwKHXDnDNEQ6AEIVDAJ#v=onepage&q=history%20of%20HKIAC&f=false|title=香港仲裁实用指南: A User's Guide|last=Moser|first=Michael J.|last2=Cheng|first2=Teresa Y. W.|date=2008-01-01|publisher=CCH Hong Kong Limited|isbn=9789881740311|language=en}}</ref> It operates under a Council composed of businesses and professionals of several nationalities. Administration of arbitration is conducted by the Secretariat through the Centre's Secretary-General. HKIAC also has an International Advisory Board to provide guidance and advice to HKIAC on a policy level.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://hkiac.org/about-us/council-members-and-committees|title=Council Members and Committees {{!}} HKIAC|website=hkiac.org|access-date=2016-11-11}}</ref>
== Case Management == HKIAC maintains one of the largest caseloads in the Asia-Pacific region, having handled over 9,000 cases since 1985. In 2016, HKIAC received a total of 460 new cases, out of which 262 were arbitrations, 183 were domain name disputes and 15 were mediations. Within the 262 arbitration cases, 94 were fully administered by HKIAC, featuring parties from 39 jurisidictions. 87.2% of new administered arbitrations were international cases. HKIAC|website=hkiac.org|access-date=2016-11-10}}</ref>
